This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for target validation and output ownership.

## Target validation

The build system supplies reachable roots and target assignments. The compiler checks that every reachable operation and external call is supported by its assigned target.

Target-contract failures are user diagnostics. Inconsistent compiler or builder metadata is an internal error.

Validation happens before lowering.

## Output ownership

Builders and lowerers return output records. The build system validates output roots, writes files, tracks manifests and removes stale files owned by the same builder and profile.

A builder cannot overwrite or clean another owner's output. Deliberate transformation requires a future explicit pipeline.

## Rewrite focus

Explain capability checking, reachability roots, pure code generation, centralised side effects and manifest ownership.

Canonical details live in both architecture authorities.
